race.comment: The penny has dropped for NATIONAL INTEREST (3) who has strung back-to-back wins together this campaign and is racing with a lot of confidence. Fitter third up and won't have to spot the leaders much of a start if he settles back in a small eight horse field. Can easily bring up the hat-trick. HURRICANE LU (11) saluted around this circuit when facing the starter for the first time and winning rider Brooker sticks. Sure to play a major role again. BROOKLYN DAISY (8) boasts a win at this track and will strip fitter third-up from the break. Has been a while since that win however has placed in five of seven runs since. Very much knocking on the door. GAGNANTE ENCHERE (9) has been thereabouts in her past few since dropping back from city level. Consider.
